CatDescriptText: Alfred Walker, dishwasher, 803 Whiteside Road, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "I believe so. They have been out so long and lost so much money that in order to catch up they have to get a raise in pay."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Alfred Walker wearing thin moustache, light colored flecked and cross hatch patterned coat, dark fedora, and dot patterned tie, standing in front of store with Coca-Cola sign
